  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "All of the necessary components for coherent detection can be integrated on a single chip.",
    "For beam steering, two integrated possibilities exist: (1) Optical phase arrays (OPAs), based on continuous tunable phase shifters and gratings 32.",
    "Bulk optics solutions, such as spinning mirrors and oscillating mirrors, have the advantage of being cheap, mature, and simple; displacing such solutions with an on-chip OPA will be a significant challenge.",
    "For an OPA to emit a single beam, the grating antennas need to be spaced less than half a wavelength (in free space)-a challenging proposition for 2D beam steering on a silicon chip.",
    "Therefore, silicon photonic OPAs typically have gratings arranged for beam steering in 1D and the wavelength of the laser is swept to steer the beam in the other direction."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For beam steering, two integrated possibilities exist: (1) Optical phase arrays (OPAs), based on continuous tunable phase shifters and gratings 32."
  ]
